  "prompt": "What should my board exam percentage be to get admission to St. Xaviers in Kolkata for a BSC in mathematics? Does St. Xaviers consider only mathematics marks as criteria for admission?",
  "response": "**Admission Criteria for BSc in Mathematics at St. Xavier's College, Kolkata:**\n\n1. **Board Exam Percentage:**  \n   While St. Xavier's College does not specify a fixed cutoff percentage, a high academic performance (typically **90% or above**) in your board exams (Class 12) is generally expected for competitive courses like BSc in Mathematics. However, the actual cutoff may vary each year based on the number of applicants and their overall performance.\n\n2. **Subject-Specific Criteria:**  \n   St. Xavier's emphasizes performance in **Mathematics** for admission to the BSc Mathematics program. A strong score in Mathematics (ideally above **90%**) is crucial. Other subjects like Physics and Chemistry (if applicable) may also be considered, depending on the specific admission guidelines for that year.\n\n3. **Entrance Exam (if applicable):**  \n   St. Xavier's may conduct an entrance exam or interview for certain programs, including BSc in Mathematics. Performance in this exam, along with your board exam scores, will determine your eligibility.\n\n4. **Holistic Evaluation:**  \n   In addition to academic scores, the college may consider other factors such as extracurricular activities, achievements, and overall profile during the admission process.\n\n**Important Notes:**  \n- Admission criteria can vary from year to year. Always check the **official St. Xavier's College website** or the admission brochure for the most updated information.  \n- Apply early and ensure you meet all eligibility criteria.  \n\nFor accurate and specific details, contact the college's admission office directly.",
